    "title": "REVIEW ON ATOMIC HABITS",
    "slug": "review-on-atomic-habits",
    "excerpt": "I've given a brief review about the book Atomic Habits by James Clear.",
    "body": "<p><a target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer nofollow\" class=\"GI370e\" href=\"https://www.google.com/search?q=Atomic+Habits&amp;sca_esv=662899ed606336e5&amp;rlz=1C1UEAD_en-GBIN1202__1202&amp;ei=U1K9af7FEqXZ5NoP3tKl8AM&amp;biw=1536&amp;bih=730&amp;ved=2ahUKEwjmn_vU066TAxV3F2IAHTnMOm4QgK4QegQIARAB&amp;uact=5&amp;oq=Atomic+Habits+brief+review&amp;gs_lp=Egxnd3Mtd2l6LXNlcnAiGkF0b21pYyBIYWJpdHMgYnJpZWYgcmV2aWV3MgYQABgWGB4yBhAAGBYYHjIGEAAYFhgeMgYQABgWGB4yCxAAGIAEGIYDGIoFMgsQABiABBiGAxiKBTILEAAYgAQYhgMYigUyCxAAGIAEGIYDGIoFMgUQABjvBTIIEAAYgAQYogRI1EJQsgZYzz9wAXgBkAEAmAGKA6ABoyaqAQQzLTEzuAEDyAEA-&amp;sclient=gws-wiz-serp&amp;mstk=AUtExfCxenIv7xLPxYOG7ImXgksUvAMPfIAPdud0ayZGBLOOSfSlDyusjtGJt0Z4Vsk3iDYSUTZWkb7Icsd_THElFM2OXgMOOwIpBQOrqkbY5P6d6h5Cz1eOVQCMbzrhWMkYGpI&amp;csui=3\"><em><u>Atomic Habits</u></em></a> by James Clear is <strong>a highly practical, top-rated guide on personal growth that advocates for small, incremental \"1% better\" daily improvements rather than massive, overnight changes</strong>. It outlines a framework for building good habits and breaking bad ones based on the four laws of behavior change: cue, craving, response, and reward.</p><p><strong><u>Key Takeaways:</u></strong></p><ul><li><p><strong>Systems Over Goals:</strong> Focus on building systems (the process) rather than just setting goals (the result).</p></li><li><p><strong>Identity-Based Habits:</strong> Long-term change occurs when you change your identity (who you believe you are) rather than just your behavior.</p></li><li><p><strong>Four Laws of Behavior Change:</strong> To make habits stick, make them obvious, attractive, easy, and satisfying.</p></li><li><p><strong>Habit Stacking:</strong> Linking new habits to existing, daily routines (e.g., \"After I brush my teeth, I will meditate for one minute\").</p></li></ul><p><strong>Environment Design:</strong> Shaping your surroundings to make positive cues visible and negative ones invisible.</p><p><strong><u>Review:</u></strong></p><ul><li><p><strong>Pros:</strong> Highly practical, easy to read, and filled with actionable advice applicable to any area of life. It blends psychology with actionable tips, making it useful for both beginners and those seeking to optimize their routines.</p></li></ul><p><strong>Cons:</strong> Some readers on Reddit find the concepts straightforward, arguing it is similar to well-known self-help advice, or that it contains some filler, notes a Reddit user.</p><p>Overall, it is widely considered a must-read for improving habits and building a better daily routine.</p>",
